	   <a name=96656576029157></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96656576029157><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>Starting stats and learning skills...</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=430><span id= >Geiden</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>6 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 17th 10:29 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.08]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2><br> Most people who start a new monk end up wishing they had put points in one stat rather than in another because they just didnt know what stats were important to a monk. Hopefully the following advice will be helpful to anyone wishing to start a monk.<br><br> There are only two races that can be monks; Humans and Iksar. <br><br> Human Monks have the following stats prior to using bonus points:&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>      STR:80  STA:80  AGI:85  WIS:75  INT:75  CHA:75<br><br> Monks get 20 bonus points to distribute among their stats. If you are playing a Human Monk I'd suggest putting 10 points into STR and the other 10 into AGI. Strength determines how hard you hit as well as how often you hit. Agility determines how often your combat skills (ie, Double Attack, Duel Wield, Block, etc.) are successful as well as determining the rate in which those Combat skills raise in level. <br><br> I would not put points into Dexterity, because 1.) Dexterity raising items are generally fairly cheap and 2.) Dexterity only determines Ranged Attack and the rate an item procs (rate an item's effect goes off in combat). You won't likely be getting any useful weapons that proc until well into your teens or twenties so I wouldn't worry about that right away. I wouldn't put skills into Stamina because every 2 points put into the stat supposedly results in 1 additional HP. While the extra HP's will definitely help in the newbie levels, at higher levels you'd much rather not get hit than try to soak damage. I'd definitely choose the AGI over the STA.<br><br> Iksar Monks have the following stats prior to spending bonus points:<br>       STR:75  STA:75  AGI:100  DEX:95  WIS:80  INT:75  CHA:55<br><br> In the case of the Iksar I'd put all of my points into Strength. The starting Agility is already 100 and thats quite good to start with. I'd avoid the other stats due to the same reasons as above.<br><br>  Should any new monks have questions or elder monks wish to comment please feel free to email. I believe all of the information on how the stats work to be accurate, but should anyone have proof otherwise please correct me.<br><br> Geiden<br>&nbsp;<br> "I like a man who grins when he fights..."<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;                                   - Winston Churchil</td></tr>
