	   <tr><td colspan=2>As mentioned previously I have two monks.&nbsp;&nbsp;The first (human) had points divided into AGI, STR, DEX, and STA.  I wish there had been sites that would have stopped me...  While my monk does do a nice amount of damage and is able to miss some blows, it has become obvious (because of Kunark) that monks need to focus on STR and items that have good AC/STR on them.  Our innate AC boost from AGI is nice, but we, for the most part, cannot adventure without going over weight (even with 2 tink bags).  <br><br>My second monk (iksar) was fully loaded with all points into STR and he does hit harder than my human monk did at his level.  However, the Iksar is hit more often and the skill checks seem to be a bit slower too...and I have finally noticed the XP penalty...hehe<br><br>AGI is nice, but with the direction the game has gone, monks are now being pushed in a more offensive direction rather than supplemental or even defensive...  In Kunark I was rarely needed to pull, unless someone wanted to split a spawn or space out timing.  In fact the only place in Kunark where FD pulling was used a lot was Karnor's...<br><br>Also, STR gear seems to be a bit tougher to find, especially with any AC attached.  AGI gear is everywhere and the prices are going down, down, down...  even serp bracers are going for less than 100p these days (at least on my server)...<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
